{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "It Is Good to Sing Praises"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Hallelujah![^290]\nHow good it is to sing praises to our God, how pleasant and lovely to praise Him!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The LORD builds up Jerusalem; He gathers the exiles of Israel."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He heals the brokenhearted and binds up their wounds."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He determines the number of the stars; He calls them each by name."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Great is our Lord, and mighty in power; His understanding has no limit."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The LORD sustains the humble, but casts the wicked to the ground."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Sing to the LORD with thanksgiving; make music on the harp to our God,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "who covers the sky with clouds, who prepares rain for the earth,\nwho makes grass to grow on the hills."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He provides food for the animals, and for the young ravens when they call."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He does not delight in the strength of the horse; He takes no pleasure in the legpower of the man."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The LORD is pleased with those who fear Him, who hope in His loving devotion."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Exalt the LORD, O Jerusalem; praise your God, O Zion!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For He strengthens the bars of your gates and blesses the children within you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He makes peace at your borders; He fills you with the finest wheat."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He sends forth His command to the earth; His word runs swiftly."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He spreads the snow like wool; He scatters the frost like ashes;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He casts forth His hail like pebbles.[^291] Who can withstand His icy blast?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He sends forth His word and melts them; He unleashes His winds, and the waters flow."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He declares His word to Jacob, His statutes and judgments to Israel."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has done this for no other nation; they do not know His judgments.[^292]\nHallelujah!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}